{"INCLASP":[{"def":"To clasp within; to hold fast to; to embrace or encircle.","pos":""}],"INCLAUDENT":[{"def":"Not closing or shutting.","pos":""}],"INCLAVATED":[{"def":"Set; fast; fixed.","pos":""}],"INCLAVE":[{"def":"Resembling a series of dovetails; -- said of a line of division, such as the border of an ordinary.","pos":""}],"INCLEMENCY":[{"def":"The state or quality of being inclement; want of clemency; want of mildness of temper; unmercifulness; severity.","pos":""},{"def":"Physical severity or harshness (commonly in respect to the elements or weather); roughness; storminess; rigor; severe cold, wind, rain, or snow.","pos":""}],"INCLEMENT":[{"def":"Not clement; destitute of a mild and kind temper; void of tenderness; unmerciful; severe; harsh.","pos":""},{"def":"Physically severe or harsh (generally restricted to the elements or weather); rough; boisterous; stormy; rigorously cold, etc.","pos":""}],"INCLEMENTLY":[{"def":"In an inclement manner.","pos":""}],"INCLINABLE":[{"def":"Leaning; tending.","pos":""},{"def":"Having a propensity of will or feeling; leaning in disposition; disposed; propense; as, a mind inclinable to truth.","pos":""}],"INCLINABLENESS":[{"def":"The state or quality of being inclinable; inclination.","pos":""}],"INCLINATION":[{"def":"The angle made by two lines or planes; as, the inclination of the plane of the earth's equator to the plane of the ecliptic is about 23º 28'; the inclination of two rays of light.","pos":""},{"def":"Decantation, or tipping for pouring.","pos":""}],"INCLINATORY":[{"def":"Having the quality of leaning or inclining; as, the inclinatory needle.","pos":""}],"INCLINE":[{"def":"To deviate from a line, direction, or course, toward an object; to lean; to tend; as, converging lines incline toward each other; a road inclines to the north or south.","pos":""}],"INCLINED":[{"def":"Making an angle with some line or plane; -- said of a line or plane.","pos":""},{"def":"Bent out of a perpendicular position, or into a curve with the convex side uppermost.","pos":""}],"INCLINER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, inclines; specifically, an inclined dial.","pos":""}],"INCLINING":[{"def":"Same as Inclined, 3.","pos":""}],"INCLINNOMETER":[{"def":"An apparatus to determine the inclination of the earth's magnetic force to the plane of the horizon; -- called also inclination compass, and dip circle.","pos":""}],"INCLIP":[{"def":"To clasp; to inclose.","pos":""}],"INCLOISTER":[{"def":"To confine as in a cloister; to cloister.","pos":""}],"INCLOSE":[{"def":"To surround; to shut in; to confine on all sides; to include; to shut up; to encompass; as, to inclose a fort or an army with troops; to inclose a town with walls.","pos":""},{"def":"To put within a case, envelope, or the like; to fold (a thing) within another or into the same parcel; as, to inclose a letter or a bank note.","pos":""}],"INCLOSER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, incloses; one who fences off land from common grounds.","pos":""}],"INCLOSURE":[{"def":"The act of inclosing; the state of being inclosed, shut up, or encompassed; the separation of land from common ground by a fence.","pos":""},{"def":"That which is inclosed or placed within something; a thing contained; a space inclosed or fenced up.","pos":""}],"INCLOUD":[{"def":"To envelop as in clouds; to darken; to obscure.","pos":""}],"INCLUDE":[{"def":"To confine within; to hold; to contain; to shut up; to inclose; as, the shell of a nut includes the kernel; a pearl is included in a shell.","pos":""},{"def":"To comprehend or comprise, as a genus the species, the whole a part, an argument or reason the inference; to contain; to embrace; as, this volume of Shakespeare includes his sonnets; he was included in the invitation to the family; to and including page twenty-five.","pos":""}],"INCLUDED":[{"def":"Inclosed; confined.","pos":""}],"INCLUDIBLE":[{"def":"Capable of being included.","pos":""}],"INCLUSA":[{"def":"A tribe of bivalve mollusks, characterized by the closed state of the mantle which envelops the body.","pos":""}],"INCLUSION":[{"def":"A foreign substance, either liquid or solid, usually of minute size, inclosed in the mass of a mineral.","pos":""}],"INCLUSIVE":[{"def":"Inclosing; encircling; surrounding.","pos":""},{"def":"Comprehending the stated limit or extremes; as, from Monday to Saturday inclusive, that is, taking in both Monday and Saturday; -- opposed to exclusive.","pos":""}],"INCLUSIVELY":[{"def":"In an inclusive manner.","pos":""}]}